    <EngDesc display="true" value="A heap-based buffer overflow vulnerability exists in the sadmind service within the Sun Solaris operating system. The vulnerability is due to an input validation error when allocating a heap buffer while parsing specially crafted RPC requests. A remote unauthenticated attacker can leverage this vulnerability by sending a crafted RPC message to the target host, to potentially inject and execute arbitrary code with root level privileges.            In a sophisticated attack case where code injection and execution is successful, the behaviour of the target is entirely dependent on the intended function of the injected code. The code in such a case would execute within the security context of the affected service, normally root.            In case if the code execution is not achieved, the sadmind service will be terminated abnormally. (IPv6 Version)"/>
